From b99e88d6d1424555422496e966f032bc4f12499d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Eli Hughes <ehughes@wavenumber.net>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 16:28:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] plotters: add RECORDER_PLOTTER for IR cross-validation

Introduce a non-rendering PLOTTER subclass that serialises every PLOTTER
virtual call as a JSON document (schema kicad.plotter_recorder.v1).
Used to cross-validate external tooling that reproduces the KiCad
plotter pipeline against a frozen golden-output corpus.

Coordinates are emitted in KiCad internal units (nm) exactly as
received from the caller; no scaling, transformation, or filtering is
applied. GetPlotterType() returns PLOT_FORMAT::UNDEFINED so the
recorder does not collide with the [FIRST_FORMAT, LAST_FORMAT] range
used by user-facing plot dialogs.

Implements all 18 PLOTTER pure virtuals plus the optional Arc (both
overloads), BezierCurve, ThickSegment, ThickArc, PlotImage, Text,
SetPageSettings, StartBlock and EndBlock overrides relevant to
schematic and PCB plot output. EndPlot() flushes the recorded ops
list to the configured FILE*.

No existing plot path is altered; the new class is purely additive
and must be invoked explicitly by callers that opt in to the
instrumentation.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
